1
00:00:06,289 --> 00:00:08,541
‐ I've jumped
far too many times.

2
00:00:08,541 --> 00:00:10,960
Erymanthos has linked
every alternative

3
00:00:10,960 --> 00:00:13,296
for the culmination
of this battle.

4
00:00:13,296 --> 00:00:15,381
The potential energy
of every outcome

5
00:00:15,381 --> 00:00:17,050
will accumulate,

6
00:00:17,050 --> 00:00:21,304
imploding into
the first timeline to give way.

7
00:00:21,304 --> 00:00:23,056
Ugh!

8
00:00:23,056 --> 00:00:24,682
[Bellcross growling]

9
00:00:24,682 --> 00:00:26,476
[cries out]

10
00:00:26,476 --> 00:00:27,727
‐ Take my hand!

11
00:00:27,727 --> 00:00:29,979
‐ Run away, Mehitak.

12
00:00:29,979 --> 00:00:31,606
Run away!

13
00:00:31,606 --> 00:00:33,024
Right now!

14
00:00:35,652 --> 00:00:37,445
[explosion booms]

15
00:00:37,445 --> 00:00:40,114
[Bellcross growls]

16
00:00:40,114 --> 00:00:43,534
[explosion booms]

17
00:00:43,534 --> 00:00:45,745
‐ Karkinos!

18
00:00:45,745 --> 00:00:47,413
‐ No! Age!

19
00:00:47,413 --> 00:00:50,416
<i>["Gravitation" by Angela]</i>

20
00:00:50,416 --> 00:00:53,503
[woman singing in Japanese]

21
00:02:17,378 --> 00:02:20,465
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

22
00:02:20,465 --> 00:02:27,096
<i>♪ ♪</i>

23
00:02:29,348 --> 00:02:32,435
[Bellcross roars]

24
00:02:33,811 --> 00:02:36,689
Something's... wrong.

25
00:02:36,689 --> 00:02:39,859
‐ What? What is it?
What are you feeling?

26
00:02:39,859 --> 00:02:42,445
<i>♪ ♪</i>

27
00:02:42,445 --> 00:02:44,197
‐ It's Age.

28
00:02:44,197 --> 00:02:49,285
<i>♪ ♪</i>

29
00:02:49,285 --> 00:02:52,538
[high‐pitched ringing]

30
00:02:59,962 --> 00:03:02,632
‐ [gasps]
Lecty!

31
00:03:04,258 --> 00:03:06,928
Wake up! Please!

32
00:03:09,847 --> 00:03:15,353
<i>♪ ♪</i>

33
00:03:17,480 --> 00:03:19,148
‐ Mm.

34
00:03:22,026 --> 00:03:23,736
‐ You bastard.

35
00:03:23,736 --> 00:03:27,281
[Bellcross growling]

36
00:03:30,785 --> 00:03:32,745
<i>♪ ♪</i>

37
00:03:43,047 --> 00:03:46,133
[shimmering and tinkling]

38
00:04:00,773 --> 00:04:03,734
<i>[militaristic music]</i>

39
00:04:03,734 --> 00:04:07,905
‐ We must continue
pushing forward at all costs!

40
00:04:07,905 --> 00:04:09,156
The time has come.

41
00:04:09,156 --> 00:04:11,450
We are now within reach
of our home world.

42
00:04:11,450 --> 00:04:13,119
My friends, hear me when I say

43
00:04:13,119 --> 00:04:15,955
that ours will be the destiny
of righteous conquerors.

44
00:04:15,955 --> 00:04:18,958
Behold!
The red god of war himself

45
00:04:18,958 --> 00:04:21,919
hails to us
as if to bless our advancement.

46
00:04:21,919 --> 00:04:25,047
We dare not shrink
from such fortune.

47
00:04:25,047 --> 00:04:29,135
Atalantes, the order,
if you please.

48
00:04:29,135 --> 00:04:30,636
‐ Attention, all fleets.

49
00:04:30,636 --> 00:04:33,556
The enemy will doubtless rally
in our wake.

50
00:04:33,556 --> 00:04:37,727
All ships are to maintain
full speed along the Starway.

51
00:04:37,727 --> 00:04:38,936
Those bringing up the rear

52
00:04:38,936 --> 00:04:40,897
are to deploy
around the flagship.

53
00:04:40,897 --> 00:04:43,649
Everyone,
assume battle formation!

54
00:04:43,649 --> 00:04:45,818
‐ This hardly seems
like a wise strategy.

55
00:04:45,818 --> 00:04:47,445
It's risky.

56
00:04:47,445 --> 00:04:51,365
The Nodos ultimately rendered
the Starway unstable, after all.

57
00:04:51,365 --> 00:04:54,535
‐ Those imbeciles
will be the death of us all.

58
00:04:54,535 --> 00:04:56,329
They're obviously
just making it up

59
00:04:56,329 --> 00:05:00,249
as they go along‐‐
this mission is suicide.

60
00:05:00,249 --> 00:05:01,626
‐ Then, we intervene?

61
00:05:01,626 --> 00:05:03,961
‐ No. Not yet.
First, we investigate

62
00:05:03,961 --> 00:05:05,755
the Starway's instability.

63
00:05:05,755 --> 00:05:09,342
We need to start by figuring
a way out of the mess we're in.

64
00:05:09,342 --> 00:05:11,469
Then we seize control.

65
00:05:11,469 --> 00:05:14,847
[space roaring]

66
00:05:14,847 --> 00:05:18,851
MAN: The Nodos approaches.
What must be done?

67
00:05:18,851 --> 00:05:21,646
‐ The Iron Tribe
must be destroyed.

68
00:05:21,646 --> 00:05:24,357
<i>[intense music]</i>

69
00:05:24,357 --> 00:05:25,816
‐ Oh, no.

70
00:05:34,617 --> 00:05:39,914
YUTY:
Karkinos, why do you not resist?

71
00:05:39,914 --> 00:05:41,207
It can't be!

72
00:05:41,207 --> 00:05:42,541
‐ Frenzy.

73
00:05:42,541 --> 00:05:44,001
YUTY: He is restraining himself

74
00:05:44,001 --> 00:05:46,796
to avoid contamination
by the fifth's madness.

75
00:05:46,796 --> 00:05:48,381
He can't hold on for long.

76
00:05:48,381 --> 00:05:50,883
I must put an end to this!

77
00:05:50,883 --> 00:05:52,718
‐ Are you troubled?

78
00:05:52,718 --> 00:05:54,845
An uninjured Nodos remains.

79
00:05:54,845 --> 00:05:57,390
‐ Mehitak cannot face
the fifth alone!

80
00:05:57,390 --> 00:05:58,557
Send me!

81
00:05:58,557 --> 00:06:00,601
<i>♪ ♪</i>

82
00:06:00,601 --> 00:06:02,311
[gasps]

83
00:06:03,771 --> 00:06:07,358
<i>♪ ♪</i>

84
00:06:07,358 --> 00:06:12,280
‐ To think... to think,
I cannot find you anywhere.

85
00:06:12,280 --> 00:06:14,198
Oh, Age.

86
00:06:14,198 --> 00:06:17,285
[shimmering and tinkling]

87
00:06:22,707 --> 00:06:26,919
<i>♪ ♪</i>

88
00:06:26,919 --> 00:06:29,922
[lasers blasting]

89
00:06:37,805 --> 00:06:40,433
MAN:
The enemy Nodos has gone mad.

90
00:06:40,433 --> 00:06:43,060
We are in danger.

91
00:06:43,060 --> 00:06:45,938
‐ The Iron Tribe must not
be allowed to advance.

92
00:06:45,938 --> 00:06:48,107
More worlds
will only be destroyed.

93
00:06:48,107 --> 00:06:52,111
Their very existence
threatens this galaxy.

94
00:06:52,111 --> 00:06:59,118
<i>♪ ♪</i>

95
00:07:16,469 --> 00:07:18,637
[insects fluttering]

96
00:07:21,932 --> 00:07:23,309
‐ What are you afraid of?

97
00:07:23,309 --> 00:07:25,102
Break through it!

98
00:07:25,102 --> 00:07:28,147
Withdrawal is not
an option for us!

99
00:07:28,147 --> 00:07:30,900
Hold the line!
Do not break for it!

100
00:07:32,485 --> 00:07:33,694
‐ That's insane.

101
00:07:33,694 --> 00:07:35,154
They charged headlong
into battle

102
00:07:35,154 --> 00:07:36,864
without waiting for backup?

103
00:07:36,864 --> 00:07:39,366
‐ No doubt
it was Meleagros' order.

104
00:07:39,366 --> 00:07:42,578
In the meantime, Age is fighting
out there all by himself.

105
00:07:42,578 --> 00:07:46,040
Seems that the fleet is content
to leave him well behind.

106
00:07:46,040 --> 00:07:48,292
‐ Those reckless idiots.

107
00:07:48,292 --> 00:07:50,419
‐ Mm.

108
00:07:51,837 --> 00:07:55,382
‐ There's no logic
in their strategy.

109
00:07:55,382 --> 00:07:56,759
If this continues,

110
00:07:56,759 --> 00:07:59,845
the Earth will become
a war zone.

111
00:07:59,845 --> 00:08:03,599
‐ Princess, haven't you given
Meleagros and Atalantes

112
00:08:03,599 --> 00:08:06,143
the benefit of the doubt
long enough?

113
00:08:06,143 --> 00:08:07,853
‐ What are you saying?

114
00:08:07,853 --> 00:08:10,481
‐ Forgive me for saying so,
Princess,

115
00:08:10,481 --> 00:08:13,234
but your brothers have made
an absolute mockery

116
00:08:13,234 --> 00:08:16,195
of the Yunos family name,
and now their arrogance

117
00:08:16,195 --> 00:08:19,907
stands to threaten
the entire human race.

118
00:08:19,907 --> 00:08:21,784
‐ You speak the truth.

119
00:08:21,784 --> 00:08:23,869
How could I ever fault you
for that?

120
00:08:23,869 --> 00:08:26,664
In their ignorance,
my brothers would sooner destroy

121
00:08:26,664 --> 00:08:30,209
our precious home world
than lead us to victory.

122
00:08:30,209 --> 00:08:31,710
And yet...

123
00:08:31,710 --> 00:08:33,462
‐ And yet,
you fear risking chaos

124
00:08:33,462 --> 00:08:35,214
by standing against them.

125
00:08:35,214 --> 00:08:36,799
You tolerate their incompetence

126
00:08:36,799 --> 00:08:40,219
because their warmongering
united the Alliance Council.

127
00:08:40,219 --> 00:08:42,054
Am I correct?

128
00:08:42,054 --> 00:08:43,556
‐ Yes.

129
00:08:43,556 --> 00:08:46,100
‐ So your part in all of this
is done.

130
00:08:46,100 --> 00:08:48,102
Now that you've
dutifully turned Age over

131
00:08:48,102 --> 00:08:50,104
to those better equipped
to handle him,

132
00:08:50,104 --> 00:08:52,648
there's nothing left
but to watch things unfold

133
00:08:52,648 --> 00:08:53,816
from a safe distance.

134
00:08:53,816 --> 00:08:55,860
‐ No, Aneasha!
That isn't true!

135
00:08:55,860 --> 00:08:57,403
‐ And why not?
After all,

136
00:08:57,403 --> 00:08:58,696
when everything
is said and done,

137
00:08:58,696 --> 00:09:00,197
there's no reason
to have assumed

138
00:09:00,197 --> 00:09:01,907
Age would be loyal to you.

139
00:09:01,907 --> 00:09:04,785
<i>[melancholy music]</i>

140
00:09:04,785 --> 00:09:07,705
‐ He did choose my brothers
over me.

141
00:09:07,705 --> 00:09:09,582
‐ Only because he thought,
by doing so,

142
00:09:09,582 --> 00:09:11,542
he could protect
you and the "Argonaut."

143
00:09:11,542 --> 00:09:14,545
Surely, you can see that.

144
00:09:14,545 --> 00:09:17,965
‐ Do you think so?

145
00:09:17,965 --> 00:09:20,384
I can't see him.

146
00:09:20,384 --> 00:09:23,262
Age's presence
is out of my reach now.

147
00:09:23,262 --> 00:09:28,726
I'm afraid he won't come back,
that he is lost to us.

148
00:09:28,726 --> 00:09:32,480
<i>♪ ♪</i>

149
00:09:32,480 --> 00:09:33,689
‐ From now on,

150
00:09:33,689 --> 00:09:35,483
many stars will vanish
from the sky,

151
00:09:35,483 --> 00:09:37,610
and many paths will fade away.

152
00:09:37,610 --> 00:09:40,196
But you?
You'll find the path.

153
00:09:40,196 --> 00:09:44,283
No matter how dark it gets,
you'll always lead us.

154
00:09:44,283 --> 00:09:48,120
‐ I can't even find
what path to take.

155
00:09:48,120 --> 00:09:51,290
‐ Just listen
to what your heart says.

156
00:09:51,290 --> 00:09:54,293
If Age were with us now,
that's what he'd tell you.

157
00:09:54,293 --> 00:09:56,962
And don't forget,
you still have us.

158
00:10:03,093 --> 00:10:06,639
<i>[intense music]</i>

159
00:10:06,639 --> 00:10:11,477
<i>♪ ♪</i>

160
00:10:11,477 --> 00:10:14,688
MELEAGROS: Wh‐why
are the rear units hesitating?

161
00:10:14,688 --> 00:10:17,066
Tell them all to push forward
right now!

162
00:10:17,066 --> 00:10:18,526
‐ Sir, we can't risk it.

163
00:10:18,526 --> 00:10:20,653
There are too many enemy ships
appearing at the stern.

164
00:10:20,653 --> 00:10:23,656
‐ What? Then‐‐then send in
all remaining fleets.

165
00:10:23,656 --> 00:10:27,201
‐ Brother, wait.
‐ Charge, you stinking cowards!

166
00:10:27,201 --> 00:10:30,246
‐ I said wait!
‐ What now?

167
00:10:30,246 --> 00:10:32,665
ATALANTES: The Bronze Tribe
is using the planet's moon

168
00:10:32,665 --> 00:10:33,707
as a nest.

169
00:10:33,707 --> 00:10:36,168
If we focus our firepower
there‐‐

170
00:10:36,168 --> 00:10:37,503
MELEAGROS: Don't undermine me!

171
00:10:37,503 --> 00:10:38,796
Ready the main cannons!

172
00:10:38,796 --> 00:10:41,340
‐ Something is approaching
from Sector 439.

173
00:10:41,340 --> 00:10:42,383
It's big.

174
00:10:42,383 --> 00:10:43,425
‐ What?

175
00:10:49,390 --> 00:10:51,475
<i>♪ ♪</i>

176
00:10:51,475 --> 00:10:53,310
[explosion booms]

177
00:10:59,149 --> 00:11:01,110
[high‐pitched shrieking]
‐ [gasps]

178
00:11:01,110 --> 00:11:03,696
‐ Is there something wrong?

179
00:11:03,696 --> 00:11:08,284
‐ I... I can sense Age.

180
00:11:08,284 --> 00:11:11,537
[whimpering]

181
00:11:11,537 --> 00:11:13,038
‐ Are you all right?

182
00:11:13,038 --> 00:11:14,748
‐ I'm scared.

183
00:11:14,748 --> 00:11:17,126
He isn't himself.

184
00:11:18,168 --> 00:11:21,880
<i>♪ ♪</i>

185
00:11:25,593 --> 00:11:28,679
[Bellcross roars]

186
00:11:32,224 --> 00:11:34,101
MELEAGROS: Look at that.

187
00:11:34,101 --> 00:11:35,936
That is our Nodos.

188
00:11:35,936 --> 00:11:38,981
‐ What in the hell
is wrong with him?

189
00:11:38,981 --> 00:11:41,066
[insects fluttering]

190
00:11:53,329 --> 00:11:55,706
MAN: The impact knocked
the satellite out of orbit.

191
00:11:55,706 --> 00:11:57,875
It's gonna crash
into the planet's surface.

192
00:11:57,875 --> 00:12:01,545
‐ Yes!
Now, that's what I call power.

193
00:12:01,545 --> 00:12:08,636
<i>♪ ♪</i>

194
00:12:22,483 --> 00:12:24,943
‐ What does he hope
to accomplish?

195
00:12:24,943 --> 00:12:27,446
‐ [gasps]

196
00:12:27,446 --> 00:12:30,282
Karkinos!

197
00:12:30,282 --> 00:12:33,327
[rocks cracking]

198
00:12:35,788 --> 00:12:39,792
<i>♪ ♪</i>

199
00:12:47,716 --> 00:12:50,719
MAN: Our shields won't be able
to withstand the impact!

200
00:12:50,719 --> 00:12:53,931
Sir, we've got to get all ships
to pull back immediately.

201
00:12:53,931 --> 00:12:55,099
‐ Certainly not!

202
00:12:55,099 --> 00:12:57,309
Our Nodos has dealt
a crushing blow

203
00:12:57,309 --> 00:12:58,811
to the enemy squadrons.

204
00:12:58,811 --> 00:13:00,396
‐ This is our moment of triumph.

205
00:13:00,396 --> 00:13:01,605
Do not withdraw!

206
00:13:01,605 --> 00:13:03,148
‐ If we don't
get out of here fast,

207
00:13:03,148 --> 00:13:05,109
the entire fleet
will be torn to ribbons

208
00:13:05,109 --> 00:13:06,360
by the aftershock.

209
00:13:06,360 --> 00:13:08,487
‐ What? Don't be ridiculous.

210
00:13:08,487 --> 00:13:09,655
We're fine.

211
00:13:09,655 --> 00:13:10,823
‐ Ah!

212
00:13:10,823 --> 00:13:14,118
<i>♪ ♪</i>

213
00:13:25,045 --> 00:13:28,340
[all yelling]

214
00:13:30,259 --> 00:13:33,345
[Bellcross cries out]

215
00:13:39,601 --> 00:13:42,020
‐ He's gone... into a frenzy.

216
00:13:42,020 --> 00:13:43,939
MAN: We must leave this place.

217
00:13:43,939 --> 00:13:47,234
There will be
no stopping him now.

218
00:13:47,234 --> 00:13:48,527
<i>♪ ♪</i>

219
00:13:48,527 --> 00:13:53,198
‐ Damn it.
This foolish sensation again.

220
00:13:53,198 --> 00:13:54,783
Prepare to retreat.

221
00:13:54,783 --> 00:13:58,620
Leave the Iron Tribe
to their precious savior.

222
00:13:58,620 --> 00:14:01,707
[shimmering and tinkling]

223
00:14:06,128 --> 00:14:09,214
[Bellcross roaring]

224
00:14:15,471 --> 00:14:18,432
YUTY: Mehitak, don't!

225
00:14:18,432 --> 00:14:21,351
Don't be foolish.

226
00:14:21,351 --> 00:14:25,314
‐ I have... no choice.

227
00:14:25,314 --> 00:14:26,857
I must.

228
00:14:26,857 --> 00:14:29,610
[whimpering]

229
00:14:29,610 --> 00:14:31,695
Artemia!

230
00:14:31,695 --> 00:14:38,702
<i>♪ ♪</i>

231
00:14:41,163 --> 00:14:44,583
MAN: The advance fleets
are sustaining major damage.

232
00:14:44,583 --> 00:14:46,293
‐ Wh‐why won't he stop?

233
00:14:46,293 --> 00:14:48,170
Has he gone completely mad?

234
00:14:48,170 --> 00:14:50,881
‐ Everyone brace yourselves
for a direct hit!

235
00:14:50,881 --> 00:14:53,425
[alarm blaring]

236
00:14:53,425 --> 00:14:56,595
‐ [gasps]
Get us out of here immediately!

237
00:14:56,595 --> 00:14:59,431
‐ Damn. There's no time.

238
00:14:59,431 --> 00:15:02,309
<i>♪ ♪</i>

239
00:15:02,309 --> 00:15:04,603
[Bellcross roaring]

240
00:15:04,603 --> 00:15:05,979
[both gasping and yelling]

241
00:15:05,979 --> 00:15:09,024
<i>♪ ♪</i>

242
00:15:12,361 --> 00:15:13,570
‐ What was that?

243
00:15:13,570 --> 00:15:15,322
‐ I‐I don't know.

244
00:15:15,322 --> 00:15:17,449
It almost looked like
another Nodos.

245
00:15:17,449 --> 00:15:21,662
NILVAL: That's the same monster
that destroyed Huelgoat.

246
00:15:21,662 --> 00:15:24,623
‐ And it's suddenly trying
to save us now?

247
00:15:24,623 --> 00:15:27,459
How will this affect
our strategy?

248
00:15:27,459 --> 00:15:29,086
‐ How should I know?

249
00:15:29,086 --> 00:15:31,046
Send communication
to the "Argonaut."

250
00:15:31,046 --> 00:15:32,130
Tell them everything.

251
00:15:32,130 --> 00:15:33,340
‐ Hmm.

252
00:15:33,340 --> 00:15:34,508
‐ At this rate,

253
00:15:34,508 --> 00:15:35,968
there will hardly be
anything left

254
00:15:35,968 --> 00:15:37,553
for me to work with.

255
00:15:37,553 --> 00:15:39,596
Damn those two idiots.

256
00:15:48,480 --> 00:15:50,023
‐ [gasps]

257
00:15:53,777 --> 00:15:55,821
[weeping softly]

258
00:15:57,656 --> 00:16:00,993
‐ You can talk to me, Princess.

259
00:16:00,993 --> 00:16:02,369
‐ Oh, Aneasha.

260
00:16:02,369 --> 00:16:05,747
It's all gone so terribly wrong.

261
00:16:05,747 --> 00:16:08,083
This is not Age.

262
00:16:08,083 --> 00:16:11,336
He would never do
these awful things.

263
00:16:11,336 --> 00:16:13,130
Never.

264
00:16:13,130 --> 00:16:18,677
Something has come over him,
something he cannot control.

265
00:16:18,677 --> 00:16:20,887
[sniffles]

266
00:16:20,887 --> 00:16:23,432
It's up to us.

267
00:16:23,432 --> 00:16:25,851
We must save our savior.

268
00:16:25,851 --> 00:16:27,227
MOBEEDO:
What you see in front of you

269
00:16:27,227 --> 00:16:30,022
is the latest report
from Commander Nilval.

270
00:16:30,022 --> 00:16:32,065
‐ Do you mean to say
that the Nodos is destroying

271
00:16:32,065 --> 00:16:34,651
everything in its path
indiscriminately?

272
00:16:34,651 --> 00:16:37,029
‐ Keep in mind,
there was a lag time of 50 hours

273
00:16:37,029 --> 00:16:38,822
when we received
the information.

274
00:16:38,822 --> 00:16:41,617
It's likely that Mars has been
annihilated in the interim,

275
00:16:41,617 --> 00:16:44,036
along with our forces.

276
00:16:44,036 --> 00:16:46,371
‐ Not once has Age attacked us!

277
00:16:46,371 --> 00:16:47,623
How dare you even assume

278
00:16:47,623 --> 00:16:50,208
he could be capable
of such brutality?

279
00:16:50,208 --> 00:16:51,585
‐ We can't be certain.

280
00:16:51,585 --> 00:16:55,297
What if he's showing us
his true colors now?

281
00:16:55,297 --> 00:16:57,049
‐ An excellent point.
Let's not forget,

282
00:16:57,049 --> 00:16:58,759
there's a part of him
that still belongs

283
00:16:58,759 --> 00:17:01,053
to the Heroic Tribe.

284
00:17:01,053 --> 00:17:03,096
‐ He's a monster, after all.

285
00:17:03,096 --> 00:17:04,348
‐ [growls]

286
00:17:04,348 --> 00:17:05,891
DHIANEILA: No.
‐ [gasps]

287
00:17:08,560 --> 00:17:11,355
MOBEEDO: Your Highness.

288
00:17:11,355 --> 00:17:14,358
‐ We are unworthy
to receive you.

289
00:17:14,358 --> 00:17:15,942
‐ Please, Princess.

290
00:17:15,942 --> 00:17:17,444
‐ I'll be fine.

291
00:17:17,444 --> 00:17:18,570
<i>♪ ♪</i>

292
00:17:18,570 --> 00:17:21,239
However hopeless
things may appear,

293
00:17:21,239 --> 00:17:22,783
he is our savior.

294
00:17:22,783 --> 00:17:25,202
You must have faith in him.

295
00:17:25,202 --> 00:17:26,745
‐ Well, yes, but‐‐

296
00:17:26,745 --> 00:17:27,913
‐ I will lead him away

297
00:17:27,913 --> 00:17:29,581
from the path of destruction.

298
00:17:29,581 --> 00:17:32,292
I'm going to save Age
from himself.

299
00:17:32,292 --> 00:17:34,586
‐ Lead him?
‐ You mean...

300
00:17:34,586 --> 00:17:36,046
‐ The time has come.

301
00:17:36,046 --> 00:17:38,590
Will you all join with me?

302
00:17:38,590 --> 00:17:40,175
<i>♪ ♪</i>

303
00:17:40,175 --> 00:17:41,468
‐ Of course we will.

304
00:17:41,468 --> 00:17:43,762
Princess,
may our undying devotion

305
00:17:43,762 --> 00:17:46,932
be as a light for you
in even the darkest night.

306
00:17:46,932 --> 00:17:50,227
We live to serve you.

307
00:17:50,227 --> 00:17:52,813
‐ This moment has been long
in coming for us,

308
00:17:52,813 --> 00:17:56,108
Princess Dhianeila.

309
00:17:56,108 --> 00:18:01,196
<i>♪ ♪</i>

310
00:18:12,749 --> 00:18:15,460
NILVAL: 300 hours have passed
since Mars became a battlefield.

311
00:18:15,460 --> 00:18:16,837
The planet escaped destruction

312
00:18:16,837 --> 00:18:18,630
only because of
the enemy Nodos intervention.

313
00:18:18,630 --> 00:18:21,758
Fully half of our forces
have sustained severe damage.

314
00:18:21,758 --> 00:18:24,386
The other half's condition
is currently unknown.

315
00:18:24,386 --> 00:18:26,722
We've been attempting
to route the enemy individually

316
00:18:26,722 --> 00:18:29,808
as the opportunity arises,
but likely as not,

317
00:18:29,808 --> 00:18:31,852
our fleet
will be completely wiped out

318
00:18:31,852 --> 00:18:34,396
in less than a hundred hours.

319
00:18:34,396 --> 00:18:38,442
The blame rests almost entirely
on our executive commanders

320
00:18:38,442 --> 00:18:40,861
and partly on the fact
that I failed to divest them

321
00:18:40,861 --> 00:18:43,655
of their authority
when I had the opportunity.

322
00:18:43,655 --> 00:18:45,449
To assist the Alliance Council,

323
00:18:45,449 --> 00:18:47,743
I make
this urgent recommendation‐‐

324
00:18:47,743 --> 00:18:49,786
please, Captain Mobeedo
and the "Argonaut"

325
00:18:49,786 --> 00:18:51,747
must be placed at the vanguard.

326
00:18:51,747 --> 00:18:54,166
This is Lieutenant General
Nilval Nephew.

327
00:18:54,166 --> 00:18:55,417
End communication.

328
00:18:55,417 --> 00:18:57,335
MOBEEDO:
What the hell are you doing?

329
00:18:57,335 --> 00:18:58,837
‐ [gasps]

330
00:18:58,837 --> 00:19:01,548
‐ What's this supposed to be,
a will?

331
00:19:01,548 --> 00:19:03,050
‐ Huh? No.

332
00:19:03,050 --> 00:19:04,092
MOBEEDO: Trust me,

333
00:19:04,092 --> 00:19:06,178
you don't want to die just yet.

334
00:19:06,178 --> 00:19:07,971
You'll miss all the fun.

335
00:19:07,971 --> 00:19:11,183
Our brave little princess
has taken command.

336
00:19:11,183 --> 00:19:12,350
‐ Is that so?

337
00:19:12,350 --> 00:19:13,894
‐ And the council has accepted

338
00:19:13,894 --> 00:19:15,312
your recommendation.

339
00:19:15,312 --> 00:19:17,731
Not only will the fleet
be completely reorganized

340
00:19:17,731 --> 00:19:19,566
under the princess' command,

341
00:19:19,566 --> 00:19:22,027
but counting our new allies,
Colonus and Orion,

342
00:19:22,027 --> 00:19:24,821
the fleet
will nearly double in size.

343
00:19:24,821 --> 00:19:26,615
Take my word‐‐
you'd be hard‐pressed

344
00:19:26,615 --> 00:19:29,868
to find higher spirits
in paradise right now.

345
00:19:29,868 --> 00:19:31,870
My point being
that reinforcements

346
00:19:31,870 --> 00:19:33,205
are on the way to you.

347
00:19:33,205 --> 00:19:34,539
Promise me you'll be alive

348
00:19:34,539 --> 00:19:36,708
when we get there... heh.

349
00:19:36,708 --> 00:19:38,376
‐ [sighs]

350
00:19:40,545 --> 00:19:45,300
So our guiding star
has finally awoken.

351
00:19:45,300 --> 00:19:47,928
‐ Our homeland awaits us!

352
00:19:47,928 --> 00:19:49,805
We shall push forward!

353
00:19:49,805 --> 00:19:51,765
The Earth will be mine!

354
00:19:51,765 --> 00:19:54,184
Thus will be my glory!

355
00:19:54,184 --> 00:19:55,185
[guns cocking]

356
00:19:55,185 --> 00:19:57,020
What is the meaning of this?

357
00:19:57,020 --> 00:20:00,816
NILVAL: Your so‐called destiny
has left the fleet in ruins.

358
00:20:00,816 --> 00:20:04,236
But I suppose I'll have to make
the best of what's left.

359
00:20:04,236 --> 00:20:05,612
‐ Nilval.

360
00:20:05,612 --> 00:20:07,739
‐ If you have anything
resembling good sense

361
00:20:07,739 --> 00:20:10,075
between you,
you'll come along peacefully.

362
00:20:10,075 --> 00:20:13,662
‐ This is a willful act
of sedition!

363
00:20:13,662 --> 00:20:14,913
‐ Not quite.

364
00:20:14,913 --> 00:20:16,623
Allow me
to convey a message to you

365
00:20:16,623 --> 00:20:20,001
on behalf
of the Yunos royal family.

366
00:20:21,294 --> 00:20:22,963
‐ Dhianeila.

367
00:20:22,963 --> 00:20:24,673
‐ Please try to understand.

368
00:20:24,673 --> 00:20:25,882
You've left me no choice

369
00:20:25,882 --> 00:20:28,009
but the course of action
before us.

370
00:20:28,009 --> 00:20:30,095
‐ You traitorous upstart!

371
00:20:30,095 --> 00:20:34,141
‐ Brothers,
I beg forgiveness of you,

372
00:20:34,141 --> 00:20:36,476
but this must not continue.

373
00:20:36,476 --> 00:20:39,604
You have disgraced us‐‐
our name,

374
00:20:39,604 --> 00:20:41,815
the posts
that have been entrusted to you,

375
00:20:41,815 --> 00:20:44,985
the very principles
for which we stand.

376
00:20:44,985 --> 00:20:46,319
It must end here.

377
00:20:46,319 --> 00:20:49,239
Our destiny is not a plaything!

378
00:20:49,239 --> 00:20:51,241
‐ How dare you slander me?

379
00:20:51,241 --> 00:20:53,410
I would've led us to victory!

380
00:20:53,410 --> 00:20:56,163
‐ And with this,
the Alliance Council expects

381
00:20:56,163 --> 00:20:59,166
your resignations swiftly.

382
00:20:59,166 --> 00:21:01,918
By the time this message
reaches both of you,

383
00:21:01,918 --> 00:21:04,546
the Calydonian Fleet
will be reorganized

384
00:21:04,546 --> 00:21:06,756
with me as executive commander.

385
00:21:06,756 --> 00:21:08,884
You are hereby ordered
to relinquish all authority

386
00:21:08,884 --> 00:21:11,469
to Lieutenant General Nilval
immediately.

387
00:21:11,469 --> 00:21:15,724
I advise you to do so
without incident.

388
00:21:15,724 --> 00:21:17,893
‐ Now,
who could argue with that?

389
00:21:17,893 --> 00:21:19,019
Let's go.

390
00:21:19,019 --> 00:21:22,272
[both wincing, sighing]

391
00:21:22,272 --> 00:21:29,279
<i>♪ ♪</i>

392
00:21:46,755 --> 00:21:48,673
MAN: Horoscope acquisition
in progress.

393
00:21:48,673 --> 00:21:51,676
All sails are set
for reconnaissance.

394
00:21:51,676 --> 00:21:54,554
‐ So, then, the "Argonaut"
can finally set sail

395
00:21:54,554 --> 00:21:56,139
on her maiden voyage.

396
00:21:56,139 --> 00:21:59,851
‐ But master, this is,
in fact, our 82nd voyage.

397
00:21:59,851 --> 00:22:02,687
‐ It's a figure of speech, Bee.

398
00:22:02,687 --> 00:22:05,232
I've been waiting
for her highness to take command

399
00:22:05,232 --> 00:22:06,858
for a long time.

400
00:22:06,858 --> 00:22:10,862
Something tells me this journey
will be unlike any other.

401
00:22:10,862 --> 00:22:14,241
Now, let's get out there,
make our own way.

402
00:22:14,241 --> 00:22:16,910
<i>♪ ♪</i>

403
00:22:16,910 --> 00:22:19,204
DHIANEILA: Age...

404
00:22:19,204 --> 00:22:21,414
[rockets roaring]

405
00:22:21,414 --> 00:22:24,501
<i>[epic orchestral music]</i>

406
00:22:24,501 --> 00:22:30,173
<i>♪ ♪</i>

407
00:22:30,173 --> 00:22:33,260
[shimmering and tinkling]

408
00:22:38,390 --> 00:22:41,393
<i>["Azurite" by Tae Urakabe]</i>

409
00:22:41,393 --> 00:22:44,521
[woman singing in Japanese]

410
00:23:49,127 --> 00:23:50,295
Humanity despairs

411
00:23:50,295 --> 00:23:52,964
as its last hope
lay in shambles.

412
00:23:52,964 --> 00:23:55,800
Next time on "Heroic Age,"
episode 15,

413
00:23:55,800 --> 00:23:57,469
"When the Light Falls."

